As Selma prepared to commemorate the 50th anniversary of 'Bloody Sunday,' so too did the Ku Klux Klan who've distributed almost 4,000 fliers of the organization's hate-literature to area homes over the last two weeks. 

Robert Jones, the grand dragon for the Loyal White Knights of the KKK confirmed the campaign in press interviews. 

'We pretty much put out fliers, some against King and some against immigration,' he told reporters. 'It's time for the American people to wake up to these falsehoods that they preach about MLK.'

