At AL.com, Jones went on to claims bags with the flier and a rock - the latter meant as paperweight - were thrown at people's homes from passing cars. 

Meanwhile thousands came to Selma to walk over the Edmund Pettus Bridge to honor the battle between police and civil rights leaders. 

'Everybody has a right to gather in this country, freedom of speech,' he said of the Selma gathering, adding that the marchers commemorating Martin Luther King, Jr.'s work and legacy were 'supporting a man they don't know about.'

